In this article, President Trump announces that Mick Mulvaney, the Director of the Office of Management and Budget (OMB), will be serving as the Acting Director of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB). The President believes that Mulvaney will take a practical approach to leading the CFPB, enabling consumers to make their own financial choices and promoting investment in communities. Mulvaney will serve as Acting Director until a permanent director is nominated and confirmed.